<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Luis Suarez scored fifteen minutes into his Atletico Madrid debut after coming on as a second-half substritute in the 5-1 thrashing of Granada. </p>

<p>Diego Costa, Angel Correa, Joao Felix and Marcus Llorente goals had given the hosts an unassailable lead before Suarez came off the bench on 70 minutes. </p>

<p>The Uruguayan, who completed a £5.5million move from Barcelona this week, headed in from six yards to make it five for Diego Simeone's side, two minutes before Jorge Molina netted a late consolation. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>
